records.addlTxt:
State files an Amended Information with 2 additional counts 4 and 5 charging possess THC, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(e) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   Motion granted.  
Count 3 - Possess THC - No contest plea. 
Count 4 - Possess THC - No contest plea. 
Count 5 - Possess THC - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 2 in the Amended Information.   Motion granted.   Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
4) Have no association with any known drug users or dealers;
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) On Count 3 - Thirty (30) days jail; Five (5) days, under the Huber Law, to commence on 10-11-16 at 5:00 p.m.   Twenty-five (25) days, stayed, to be imposed upon the discretion of the agent.   Transfer to Sheboygan County Jail or Calumet County Jail is authorized or in the alternative travel outside the county for purposes of employment.  
Mintues.
